      "raw_text": "Levi G. Monroe, secretary of the\nchamber of commerce, returned\nyesterday from Olympia, where he\nhad been in the interest of several\nbills effecting this locality. Mr.\nMonroe says he feels certain of the\nappointment of Representative l..\nP. Hornberger by the governor as\none Of the commissioners for the\nAlaska Yukon Pacific exposition.\nSenators Rosenhaupt and Scott of\nthis county are also spoken of as\npossibilities."
